Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @black beans{1} in a #sieve{}.

Zest and cut the @lime{1} into wedges. Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 1cm chunks (no need to peel!).

 == Roasting the Sweet Potato ==

Pop the sweet potato chunks onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{18-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

== Making the Dal ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the garlic and @North Indian style spice mix{2}. Stir and cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @red split lentils{50}, black beans and @tomato puree{30}, cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @vegetable stock paste{15} and @water{450} for the dal to the pan and stir to combine.

Bring to a simmer, cover with a #lid{} and cook, stirring frequently, until the lentils are soft, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Stir regularly to make sure they don't stick to the bottom of the pan and add a splash of water if it gets too thick.

== Warming the Naans ==

When the dal is almost cooked, pop the @plain naans{2} onto a baking tray.

Spread each with the @butter{10}(g) and pop into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Finishing the Dal ==

Once roasted, stir the sweet potato through the dal. Add the @baby spinach{40} a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

When the dal's ready, remove from the heat. Squeeze in half the lime juice, then stir in the lime zest and three quarters of the @creme fraiche{75}. Taste and season if needed.

Share your dal between your #bowls{} and top with a dollop of the remaining creme fraiche.

Serve with the naans for dipping and scooping, along with any remaining lime wedges. Enjoy!